parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or shutting off can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off while driving
often after filling up the gas tank
and may be accompanied by warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates
slips
or fails to engage
often accompanied by warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system overheating can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure.
symptoms: The engine overheats
often accompanied by warning lights on the dashboard
and may be caused by a faulty coolant sensor or other issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch problems can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
or the vehicle hesitates or stalls when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition or keyless entry problems can cause the vehicle to start or shut off unexpectedly, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle starts or shuts off without the key being present
or the keyless entry system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates while shifting gears
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle rolls backwards on a hill.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or have difficulty shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The involuntary braking issue can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop or slow down, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle brakes suddenly without warning
the lights on the dashboard flicker
the gauges on the dashboard malfunction
the "Hill Assist Control" alert appears on the radio monitor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling issue can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or have difficulty restarting, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine shuts off while driving
the vehicle has difficulty restarting
the vehicle stalls after refueling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the HVAC blend door actuator can cause the engine to overheat, leading to accidents or engine damage.
symptoms: The engine overheats
the HVAC system malfunctions
the blend door actuator fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch can cause the door to open while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The door latch breaks
the door opens while driving
the door will not stay closed.
